    "statementHTML": "<div class=\"statement-body\">\n<div class=\"statement-section statement-goal\">\n   <h2><span class=\"icon icon-goal\">&nbsp;</span><span>Goal </span></h2>\n   <span class=\"question-statement\">You are given a string containing only parentheses.<br>Compute the minimum number of parentheses to add so that the resulting string becomes balanced.<br><br>A string is balanced if:<br><br>1. Every opening parenthesis <const>(</const> has a corresponding closing parenthesis <const>)</const>.<br><br>2. They are closed in the correct order (e.g., <const>())</const> is not balanced, <const>(()</const> is not balanced).</span>\n</div>\n<div class=\"statement-section statement-protocol\">\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Input</div>\n      <div class=\"question-statement-input\">A single line: a string <var>s</var> made of only characters <const>(</const> and <const>)</const></div>\n   </div>\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Output</div>\n      <div class=\"question-statement-output\">A single integer: the minimum number of parentheses that must be added to make <var>s</var> balanced.</div>\n   </div>\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Constraints</div>\n      <div class=\"question-statement-constraints\">1 &le; length of <var>s</var> &le; 10</div>\n   </div>\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Example</div>\n      <div class=\"statement-inout\">\n         <div class=\"statement-inout-in\">\n            <div class=\"title\">Input</div>\n            <pre class=\"question-statement-example-in\">()(())</pre>\n         </div>\n         <div class=\"statement-inout-out\">\n            <div class=\"title\">Output</div>\n            <pre class=\"question-statement-example-out\">0</pre>\n         </div>\n      </div>\n   </div>\n</div>"
